baller\n*  1985   &ndash; [[T-Pain]], American rapper, producer, and actor\n*[[1986]] &ndash; [[Olivier Giroud]], French footballer\n*  1986   &ndash; [[Martin Guptill]], New Zealand cricketer\n*  1986   &ndash; [[Ben Lovett (British musician)|Ben Lovett]], Welsh musician and songwriter\n*  1986   &ndash; [[Cristi\u00e1n Zapata]], Colombian footballer\n*[[1987]] &ndash; [[Aida Garifullina]], Russian operatic soprano\n*[[1988]] &ndash; [[Egl\u0117 Stai\u0161i\u016bnait\u0117]], Lithuanian hurdler\n*[[1989]] &ndash; [[Andr\u00e9 Weis]], German footballer\n*[[1991]] &ndash; [[Thomas R\u00f6hler]], German javelin thrower<ref>{{cite web |title=Thomas R\u00f6hler|url=https://www.worldathletics.org/athletes/germany/thomas-rohler-255897|publisher=World Athletics|accessdate=7 February 2020}}</ref>\n*[[1992]] &ndash; [[Ezra Miller]], American actor and singer\n*[[1994]] &ndash; [[Aliya Mustafina]], Russian gymnast\n*[[1996]] &ndash; [[Jacob Host]], Australian rugby league player\n*[[1997]] &ndash; [[Yana Kudryavtseva]], Russian gymnast\n*  1997   &ndash; [[Max Verstappen]], Dutch Formula One driver\n*[[1998]] &ndash; [[Trevor Moran]], American youtuber and singer\n*[[2002]] &ndash; [[Maddie Ziegler]], American dancer and actress\n*  2002   &ndash; [[Levi Miller]], Australian actor and model \n<!--Do not add people without Wikipedia articles to this list. Do not trust \u201cthis year in history\u201d websites for accurate date information. Do not link multiple occurrences of the same year, just link the first occurrence.-->\n\n==Deaths==\n*[[AD 420|420]] &ndash; [[Jerome]], Roman priest, theologian, and saint (b. 347)\n* [[653]] &ndash; [[Honorius of Canterbury]], Italian archbishop and saint \n* [[940]] &ndash; [[Fan Yanguang]], Chinese general\n* [[954]] &ndash; [[Louis IV of France]] (b. 920)\n*[[1101]] &ndash; [[Anselm IV (archbishop of Milan)|Anselm IV]], Italian archbishop\n*[[1246]] &ndash; [[Yaroslav II of Vladimir]] (b. 1191)\n*[[1288]] &ndash; [[Leszek II the Black]]