ihanna-top-spotify-year-end-lists|magazine=Billboard|accessdate=March 28, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! Rank\n! Artist\n! {{abbr|Chg|Change (within a year)}}\n|-\n! 1\n| [[Drake (musician)|Drake]]<br />{{small|\u2014 4.7 billion streams}} || style=\"text-align:center\" |{{Steady}}\n|-\n! 2\n| [[Justin Bieber]] || style=\"text-align:center\" |{{Increase}}\n|-\n! 3\n| [[Rihanna]] || style=\"text-align:center\" |{{Increase}}\n|-\n! 4\n| [[Twenty One Pilots]] || style=\"text-align:center\" |{{Increase}}\n|-\n! 5\n| [[Kanye West]] || style=\"text-align:center\" |{{Steady}}\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ 2017<ref>{{cite magazine|author=Associated Press|date=December 12, 2017|title=Ed Sheeran Tops Spotify's 2017 Most-Streamed List|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/8055138/ed-sheeran-tops-spotify-2017-most-streamed-list|magazine=Billboard|accessdate=March 28, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! Rank\n! Artist\n! {{abbr|Chg|Change (within a year)}}\n|-\n! 1\n| [[Ed Sheeran]]<br />{{small|\u2014 6.3 billion streams}} || style=\"text-align:center\" |{{Increase}}\n|-\n! 2\n| [[Drake (musician)|Drake]] || style=\"text-align:center\" |{{Decrease}}\n|-\n! 3\n| [[The Weeknd]] || style=\"text-align:center\" |{{Increase}}\n|-\n! 4\n| [[Kendrick Lamar]] || style=\"text-align:center\" |{{Increase}}\n|-\n! 5\n| [[The Chainsmokers]] || style=\"text-align:center\" |{{Increase}}\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ 2018<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2018/digital/news/drake-ariana-grande-top-spotifys-year-end-wrapped-charts-1203078820/|title=Drake, Ariana Grande Top Spotify's Year-End 'Wrapped' Charts|date=December 3, 2018|accessdate=October 28, 2019|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]}}</ref>\n|-\n! Rank\n! Artist\n! {{abbr|Chg|Change (within a year)}}\n|-\n! 1 \n| [[Drake (musician)|Drake]]<br />{{small|\u2014 8.2 billion streams}} || style=\"text-align:center\" |{{Increase}}\n|-\n! 2 \n| [[Post Malone]] || style=\"text-align:center\" |{{Increase}}\n|-\n! 3 \n| [[XXXTentacion]] || style=\"t